      "content": "I see. But if we look at the data, it's pretty clear that the environmental benefits—like cleaner air and reduced congestion—are immediate and measurable. On the other hand, the economic arguments from opponents seem to rely a lot on hypothetical fears about small businesses or \"what ifs.\" Don't you think the scientific and environmental necessity of these programs should take precedence over those economic uncertainties?",
